# KBOS Go Backend

## Package layout (target)

```
cmd/kb/           # CLI entry (kb init, rebuild, search, backup, …)
internal/vault/   # path resolution, multi-vault, kb.yaml
internal/doc/     # parse markdown, frontmatter, wiki links, tasks
internal/index/   # Bleve build/query; rebuild from vault only
internal/graph/   # backlinks, relationships → .kb/graph/
internal/crypto/  # AES-256-GCM + Argon2id; documented .enc format
internal/backup/  # snapshot, verify, pluggable destinations
internal/ai/      # provider interface; RAG over markdown; citations required
internal/plugin/  # extension hooks
api/              # REST + WebSocket
```

## Patterns

- Indexers watch `docs/` and write only under `.kb/`. On mismatch, prefer rebuild over silent drift.
- Use structured logging; separate audit, backup, and indexing log channels.
- CLI commands must work with no server running (`kb doctor`, `kb rebuild`, encrypt/decrypt/backup).
- Scale target: 100k+ markdown files — stream/chunk FS walks; avoid loading full vault into RAM.
- Errors: wrap with context; user-facing CLI messages actionable (vault path, permission, corrupt index).

## Security

- Encryption format documented in-repo; `kb decrypt` works without UI.
- No plaintext secrets in logs; Argon2id params configurable via `config/kb.yaml`.

## Tests

- Unit: parsers, link resolution, query grammar, crypto round-trip.
- Integration: temp vault → index → search → `kb rebuild` idempotency.
